events.name: Variability in LCA studies of EVs
events.wd_label: Variability in LCA studies of EVs
events.wd_description: The results of life cycle assessment (LCA) studies about electric vehicles (EVs) vary due to several factors, including climatic conditions, data sources, battery production scale, and methodological choices. The choice of specific battery datasets, such as those for nickel sulphate, cobalt sulphate, and lithium hydroxide, also contributes to variability.
events.description: The results of life cycle assessment (LCA) studies about electric vehicles (EVs) vary due to several factors, including climatic conditions, data sources, battery production scale, and methodological choices. The choice of specific battery datasets, such as those for nickel sulphate, cobalt sulphate, and lithium hydroxide, also contributes to variability.

events.wd_description: Climatic conditions are one of the factors affecting the results of LCA studies for EVs.

events.name: Methodological choices

events.name: Importance of nickel sulphate in LIB production
events.wd_label: Importance of nickel sulphate in LIB production
events.wd_description: Nickel sulphate is a significant feedstock in the production of lithium-ion battery (LIB) cathodes. The demand for nickel sulphate is expected to increase significantly by 2030 due to the rising number of EVs and the trend toward nickel-rich LIBs.
events.description: Nickel sulphate is a significant feedstock in the production of lithium-ion battery (LIB) cathodes. The demand for nickel sulphate is expected to increase significantly by 2030 due to the rising number of EVs and the trend toward nickel-rich LIBs.

events.name: Nickel sulphate demand
events.wd_description: The global annual demand for nickel sulphate is expected to increase from less than 200 kilotons in 2022 to more than 1000 kilotons by 2030.
events.description: The global annual demand for nickel sulphate is expected to increase from less than 200 kilotons in 2022 to more than 1000 kilotons by 2030.

events.name: Environmental impact
events.wd_description: Nickel sulphate as an active material of the cathode contributes significantly to the environmental impact of LIBs.

events.name: Analysis of nickel sulphate datasets in LCA studies
events.wd_label: Analysis of nickel sulphate datasets in LCA studies
events.wd_description: This study analyzes the production of nickel sulphate based on different datasets used in LCA studies. The variability in global warming potential (GWP100) and terrestrial acidification results is explored, along with the impact of energy mix and recycled nickel usage.

events.name: Energy mix impact

events.wd_description: There is a need for technology-specific and ore-grade-specific primary data to model representative supply chain configurations. If primary data is not available, process simulations can be used to acquire necessary data.

events.name: Future LCI approach and the SIMTEGRAL project
events.wd_label: Future LCI approach and the SIMTEGRAL project
events.wd_description: Future life cycle inventory (LCI) studies should follow a transparent and modular approach. The SIMTEGRAL project aims to develop process simulations of specific gate-to-gate processes in battery supply chains to generate necessary life cycle inventory data.
